  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing Urgent Humanitarian Needs for Internally Displaced Populations in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM continues to contribute to improved and dignified living conditions of the populations affected by the crisis through the provision of life-saving assistance to address humanitarian needs in the most affected governorates of Iraq. IOM is delivering targeted and quality services, based on the needs and the situation of internally displaced persons, and is addressing specific needs of the populations living in protracted displacement. IOM is providing a combination of shelter (critical shelter upgrades), non-food items (basic and replacement items, in-kind and through cash-based assistance), camp coordination and camp management, health, protection, mental health and psychosocial support activities, while maintaining and strengthening the communication with the target communities.</narrative>
  </description>
